text: The Matthew Cartwright House is a historic house in Terrell, Texas. It was built in 1882-1883 for Matthew Cartwright, a rancher and banker. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since April 4, 1979. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Kaufman County, Texas Category:Houses completed in 1883 Category:1883 establishments in Texas
title: Matthew Cartwright House (Terrell, Texas)
